  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sector-Wide Impact Assessment (SWIA) for Mining in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mining, a key sector for expansion in the 2010-2014 Plan Nacional de Desarollo, has the potential to contribute significantly to Colombia&#x2019;s economic and social development. It is a crucial source of potential revenue for growth, fiscal stability and financing public services and regional development. However, widespread human rights-related, social and environmental risks exist within the sector. Therefore, a Sector-Wide Impact Assessment (SWIA) is needed which analyses the relation between the mining sector and human rights that needs to be understood in order to strengthen public policy, national planning, and the efforts of national interest groups and stakeholders in order to facilitate the emergence, promotion and follow-up stakeholder recognition and take up of recommendations for better policies and practices. The SWIA has been conducted by Institute for Human Rights and Business (IHRB) / Centro Regional de Empresas y Emprendimientos Responsables (CREER).The project resulted in : 1.	A comprehensive analysis which has been made publicly available: https://www.ihrb.org/focus-areas/commodities/report-sector-wide-impact-assessment-of-the-mining-swia-in-colombia http://creer-ihrb.org/proyectos-eisi.2.	A trusted, impartial space for dialogue.3.	Potential benchmarks for stronger policy approaches and stakeholder practice.4.	Insights for possible entry points to widen/deepen participation and address gaps in mining decision-making.5.	Enhanced expertise on business and human rights.</narrative>
  </description>
